Package imos

Interface Summary
IAct An act is the association of a schema with the feedback the agent receives when trying to enact that schema.
IActivation An activation consists of the activated act and a weight that determines the strength of the activation.
IActProposition A proposition of in intention act.
IDecider A decider decides what interaction to try to enact next when the previous decision cycle is over based on the current state of sequential and spatial memory
IEnaction A structure used to manage the enaction of a scheme in the real world or the simulation of the enaction of a scheme in spatial memory.
IImos The Intrinsically Motivated Schema mechanism (Ernest's sequential system).
IProposition A proposal that Ernest enacts a schema.
ISchema A Schema is a sequence of interaction between Ernest and its environment.
 

Class Summary
Act An act is the association of a schema with the feedback the agent receives when trying to enact that schema.
Activation An activation consists of the activated act and a weight that determines the strength of the activation.
ActProposition A proposition of in intention act.
Decider This is the regular decider for Ernest 7 that does not use spatial memory.
Decider11 A decider decides what interaction to try to enact next when the previous decision cycle is over based on the current state of sequential and spatial memory
Decider12 Decider for Ernest 12.
Enaction A structure used to manage the enaction of a scheme in the real world or the simulation of the enaction of a scheme in spatial memory.
Imos The Intrinsically Motivated Schema mechanism.
Proposition Represents a proposal for enacting a Schema.
Schema A Schema is a sequence of interaction between Ernest and its environment.
